SED stands for Stream EDitor
It is a simple yet powerful utility that parses the text and transforms it seamlessly.
SED was developed during 1973â€“74 by Lee E. McMahon of Bell Labs.

GNU SED - SED is written and maintained by the Free Software Foundation (FSF) and it is distributed by GNU/Linux.
Beauty of SED - Once you get familiar with its syntax, you can solve many complex tasks with a few lines of SED script.

SED can be used in many different ways, such as:

i. Text substitution,
ii. Selective printing of text files,
iii. In-a-place editing of text files,
iv. Non-interactive editing of text files, and many more.